lyrics:
(Verse)
She sells seashells by the seashore, said Sally Sue,
But Peter Piper picked a peck of pickled peppers, too.
Round the rugged rocks the ragged rascals ran,
While Betty Botter bought some butter, just as planned.

(Chorus)
Tongue tied, twisted, tangled in twisters,
Words whirl like a whirlwind, wild and mysterious.
How much wood would a woodchuck chuck, if a woodchuck could chuck wood?
Fuzzy Wuzzy was a bear, but Fuzzy Wuzzy had no hair, misunderstood.
